The strongest part of this design is actually not the anomaly detection.

Anomaly detection is commoditized.

The differentiator is:

KRYLO creates a machine-readable map of emerging structural transitions before narrative consensus forms.

The tsunami layer detects the disturbance.

The earthquake layer explains the stress field.

The causal graph explains propagation.

The CRI determines whether the disturbance has enough independent structural energy to matter.

The final product is not a predictor.

It is a causal observatory.

That aligns very closely with the original KRYLO premise: surface leverage before it becomes obvious.


